data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataAddCategoryStoredProcNameDescription
data.value: The name of the stored procedure in the database that creates a new Category in the tables. The default is 'AddCategory' and is created by the scripts you can run to create the logging database.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataAddCategoryStoredProcNameDisplayName
data.value: Add Category Procedure

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataDatabaseInstanceNameDescription
data.value: The name of the Database Instance to use for logging messages, as configured in the Data Access Application Block.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataDatabaseInstanceNameDisplayName
data.value: Database Instance

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataDescription
data.value: A logging target listener that sends log messages to a specified database using a database instance configured in the Data Access Application Block.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataDisplayName
data.value: Database Trace Listener

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataFilterDescription
data.value: The minimum severity of messages that will be sent to the logging target. Valid values are All (the default), Off, Critical, Error, Warning, Information, Verbose, and Activity Tracing. The behavior is for messages with the selected severity and all higher severities to be included. For example, the Warning setting will allow warning, error, and critical messages to be written to the logging target.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataFilterDisplayName
data.value: Severity Filter

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataFormatterDescription
data.value: The name of the Log Message Formatter to use to format log messages written to the database.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataFormatterDisplayName
data.value: Formatter

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataListenerDataTypeNameDescription
data.value: The fully qualified type name of the Listener.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataListenerDataTypeNameDisplayName
data.value: Listener Data Type

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataNameDescription
data.value: The name of the Database Trace Listener.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataNameDisplayName
data.value: Name

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataTraceOutputOptionsDescription
data.value: Listeners that do not output to a Text Formatter use this property to determine which options, or elements, should be included in the trace output. Possible values are: CallStack, DateTime, LogicalOperationStack, None, ProcessId, ThreadId, and Timestamp. The default is None. This property is optional.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataTraceOutputOptionsDisplayName
data.value: Trace Output Options

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataTypeNameDescription
data.value: The fully qualified type name of the Database Trace Listener.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataTypeNameDisplayName
data.value: Type

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataWriteLogStoredProcNameDescription
data.value: The name of the stored procedure in the database that writes log messages into the tables. The default is 'WriteLog', and is created by the scripts you can run to create the logging database.

data.name: FormattedDatabaseTraceListenerDataWriteLogStoredProcNameDisplayName
data.value: Write To Log Procedure
